gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Nets 147, Jazz 114
gameRecap.excerpt: The Nets put up a season-high 147 points as they defeated Utah, 147-114. Ben Simmons made his return for the first time since Nov. 6 as he tallied 10 points, eight rebounds, and 11 assists as Mikal Bridges (33 points, six 3PT) and Cam Thomas (25 points, seven rebounds) added 58 points. Keyonte George led Utah with 21 points, four rebounds, and three assists. The Nets move to 19-27 as the Jazz move to 24-24.
